ADDITIONAL NOTICES

This MIT license applies only to the ParkScreen source code. It does NOT
grant rights to any datasets or third-party models used or referenced by this
project. In particular:

- NeuroVoz (Spanish PD voice corpus) is distributed under its own terms via
  Zenodo. Users of this project who wish to reproduce the training numbers
  must obtain NeuroVoz directly from Zenodo and accept the NeuroVoz Data Use
  Agreement. See `docs/DATASETS.md`.

- UFNet (ROC-HCI smile-task feature dataset) is distributed under the MIT
  License by the original authors (AAAI 2025). Users who wish to retrain the
  facial classifier should obtain the UFNet CSV directly from the ROC-HCI
  repository. See `docs/DATASETS.md`.

- YouTubePD is used for external validation only, per UFNet's shipped subset.
  See `docs/DATASETS.md`.

ParkScreen output is a **screening decision aid**, not a clinical diagnosis.
See `docs/LIMITATIONS.md` for the full framing.
